# Evaluate EfficientNet-B3 on 17-Class Dataset (OOD & Accuracy)

The goal is to evaluate the newly trained `efficientnet_b3_hog_aug` model on your [17-class](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/17-class) holdout dataset. We will integrate Mahalanobis distance calculations to detect out-of-distribution (OOD) data and measure classification performance using CLAHE preprocessing.

## Proposed Changes

### Evaluation Scripts Updates

#### [MODIFY] [compute_ood_stats.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/compute_ood_stats.py)
*   **Model Update**: Change the backbone from `efficientnet_b1` to `efficientnet_b3`.
*   **Model Path**: Target the newly trained [models_full/efficientnet_b3_hog_aug.pth](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/models_full/efficientnet_b3_hog_aug.pth).
*   **Feature Configuration**: Ensure the extra feature dimensions perfectly match the HOG-only configuration (drop GLCM if we are testing the HOG-only model first).
*   *Action*: We will run this script once on the `Combined_Dataset/Training` set to calculate the Mahalanobis statistics (class centers and covariance) for the new B3 model, saving to `models_full/ood_stats.pt`.

#### [MODIFY] [eval_new_dataset.py / eval_ood.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval_new_dataset.py)
*   **Target Dataset**: Point the script to the `17-class` dataset directory.
*   **Model Update**: Update the backbone to `efficientnet_b3` to successfully load the new weights.
*   **Preprocessing**: Ensure the `ApplyCLAHE` transform is active to match the training pipeline.
*   **Metrics**: Compute Mahalanobis distance against the statistics generated by `compute_ood_stats.py` and flag images crossing the 99th percentile threshold as OOD.
*   *Action*: Run this script to generate confusion matrices and evaluate exactly how the model performs on these unseen classes.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
*   Run `.venv/bin/python compute_ood_stats.py` to generate the new training distribution statistics.
*   Run `.venv/bin/python eval_new_dataset.py` over the `17-class` dataset to obtain accuracy, F1-scores, and the ratio of samples correctly flagged as OOD.

### Manual Verification
*   We will review the generated evaluation report and confusion matrix graphics.
